<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-12-15T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-12-15T18:00:00-05:00" n="500" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d500">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">121.5532/14: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Morgan</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-12-15T18:00:00-05:00">December 15, 1930—6
                                p.m.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>100. Your 167, December 15, 10 a.m. Blandy has now been designated as
                            Naval Attaché effective upon termination of Naval Mission about January
                            31.</p>
                        <p>Please advise Foreign Office.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>